reviews.review_text:
Wow.... Thank you This was the last show i ever went to. Sure, the sound wasn't great in '95 (especially at the Shoreline). But to go back and hear this again, especially Brokedown Palace, is worth 5 stars in my book. 

Fare you well
Fare you well
I love you more than words can tell.

Miss you, Jerry. Thanks for sending me off with such great memories. I had no idea the poignance of that encore back then, and now that I hear it again 16 years later, my heart and soul are weeping. I am, at the very least - truly grateful.
The last time... This was my last show and hearing Jerri's voice swirls up many emotions. What a wonderful journey of joy! It continues...I miss you Jerry!
My last show Sad day. We had seats pretty close, center. Jerry look and played awful. Fare the well
